        <!-- Page 2: Israel -->
        <div id="page2" class="page">
             <header class="bg-blue-600 text-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg mb-8">
                <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold">Interactive Reading: Part 2 of 2</h1>
                <p class="mt-2 text-blue-100">Topic: Israel's Successful Stock Market</p>
            </header>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <!-- Reading Text Column -->
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md space-y-4 h-screen overflow-y-auto">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-4 border-b-2 border-blue-200 pb-2">Reading Text</h2>
                    <div class="prose max-w-none text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                        <p><strong>Marc Filippino:</strong> Israel now has the world's best stock market. This is mostly because the country's economy is growing very fast. This is happening even with the conflict in Gaza and bombing in nearby countries. So, with so much criticism, why isn't the Israeli stock market changing more? Here to talk about it is FT columnist Ruchir Sharma.</p>
                        <p><strong>Ruchir Sharma:</strong> Hey, Marc.</p>
                        <p><strong>Marc Filippino:</strong> So, how well is the Israeli stock market doing?</p>
                        <p><strong>Ruchir Sharma:</strong> Well, one fact really surprised me. Since the conflict began on October 7th, 2023, the Israeli stock market is up 80 per cent in dollar terms. That's more than any other developed market in the world. So, it is the best market over the last 21 months.</p>
                        <p><strong>Marc Filippino:</strong> Yes, that is surprising. Why weren't investors affected by all of this? Why did they buy more in the Israeli market?</p>
                        <p><strong>Ruchir Sharma:</strong> I think the market sent a message. One message was that the conflict was not going to last, and Israel was going to win. The second thing is that it shows the strength of Israel's economy, which is technology. Since October 2023, there has also been a big AI tech boom.</p>
                        <p><strong>Marc Filippino:</strong> But what about the criticism? Why hasn't that affected the Israeli economy or market?</p>
                        <p><strong>Ruchir Sharma:</strong> I think the markets only look at the economy and company profits. There is also a worldwide tech boom. We see a similar thing in the US. The economy has been strong, and I think it's because of the AI boom in America.</p>
                        <p><strong>Marc Filippino:</strong> Is there anything that could shake the markets in Israel?</p>
                        <p><strong>Ruchir Sharma:</strong> If there is a new conflict, or if the current one gets worse, the market will not like that. Also, if the interest in AI technology ends, the market would have a problem.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Interactive Exercises Column -->
                <div class="space-y-8 h-screen overflow-y-auto pr-4">
                    <div class="activity-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-4">1. Useful Phrases</h3>
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700">
                            <li><b>Stock market:</b> A place where parts of companies (shares) are bought and sold.</li>
                            <li><b>Economy is growing:</b> A country is making more money and has more jobs.</li>
                            <li><b>Conflict:</b> A serious disagreement or fight.</li>
                            <li><b>Criticism:</b> Saying that you think something is bad.</li>
                            <li><b>Investors:</b> People who put money into something to make more money.</li>
                            <li><b>To win:</b> To be successful in a fight or competition.</li>
                            <li><b>Strength of the economy:</b> How well a country's economy is doing.</li>
                            <li><b>Tech boom:</b> A time when technology companies grow very quickly.</li>
                            <li><b>Have a problem:</b> To experience a difficulty or a setback.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="activity-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-700 mb-4">2. True or False?</h3>
